parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belts can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belts may lock or become stuck
making it difficult or impossible to use them; the seat belts may retract while being worn
causing discomfort and safety concerns; the seat belt anchor cable may break or fray
causing the buckle to come loose; the seat belt control module may malfunction
causing the seat belts to lock or become inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt anchor can cause the seat belt to become ineffective, leading to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt anchor cable may break or fray
causing the buckle to come loose; the seat belt anchor may become detached from the vehicle
rendering the seat belt useless.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt control module can cause the seat belts to malfunction, leading to safety concerns and potentially serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belts may lock or become stuck
making it difficult or impossible to use them; the seat belts may retract while being worn
causing discomfort and safety concerns; the seat belt control module may malfunction
causing the seat belts to lock or become inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the brakes can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes make a whistling noise
the brakes fail to engage
the vehicle is unable to stop
the brake pads wear out quickly
the rotors overheat
the brakes squeal or grind.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent wear of brake pads and rotors can lead to brake failure, accidents, and increased maintenance costs.
symptoms: The brake pads wear out quickly
the rotors overheat
the brakes squeal or grind
the vehicle requires frequent brake pad replacements.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially on wet or slippery surfaces.
symptoms: The ABS system fails to activate
the wheels fail to lock up
the brake pressure is reduced
the vehicle is unable to stop on wet or slippery surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire, which can lead to damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: The wiring harness catches fire
which may be extinguished by rain.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning alarm system can cause unnecessary stress, inconvenience, and potentially lead to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The alarm system activates multiple times automatically while the vehicle is parked
doors lock and unlock multiple times
and interior lights turn on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to become stranded, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: The key will not turn in the ignition switch
making it difficult or impossible to start the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning horn can cause unnecessary noise, disturbance, and potentially lead to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The horn goes off randomly
even when the vehicle is not in use
and can be triggered by temperature changes or other environmental factors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning remote key fob can cause inconvenience, stress, and potentially lead to safety issues.
symptoms: The remote key fob stops working
and even after replacing the battery
it still does not function properly.
